12 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
13 An Act relating to criminal disturbance; declaring
legislative findings; amending 21 O.S. 2021, Sections
14 915 and 916, which relate to disturbance of religious
meeting; specifying range of punishment for certain
15 misdemeanor offense; establishing felony offense for
certain convictions; specifying range of punishment
16 for certain felony offense; modifying elements of
certain offenses; providing for noncodification; and
17 declaring an emergency.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
22 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
23 The Legislature finds that the right of the people to meet and
24 assemble for religious worship is imperative for the people of this
