1 stat e; that the exercise of the right of a person to protest at
2 places of religious worship must be balanced against the right of
3 another person to meet and assemble for religious worship in an
4 unobstructed manner; and that preventing the willful obstruction of
5 access of a person to places of religious worship is a matter of
6 statewide concern. Therefore, the Legislature declares that it is a
7 compelling public interest of this state to protect the ability of
8 its people to meet and assemble for religious worship without
9 willful obstruction.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 915, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 915. Every person who willfully disturbs, interrupts,
13 or disquiets any assemblage of people met for religious worship, by
14 any of the acts or things hereinafter enumerated, is in Section 916
15 of this title shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
16 punishable by a fine not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
17 by imprisonment in the county jail for a term not to exceed one (1)
18 year, or by both such fine and imprisonment. A person who commits a
19 second or subsequent offense shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
20 felony punishable by a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars
21 ($1,000.00), by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of
22 Corrections for a term not to exceed two (2) years, or by both such
23 fine and imprisonment.
