1 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 916, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 916. The following are the acts deemed to constitute
4 disturbance of a religious meeting as prohibited by Section 915 of
5 this title:
6 1. Uttering any profane discourse, committing any rude or
7 indecent act, or making any unnecessary noise, either within the
8 place where such meeting is held, or so near it as to disturb the
9 order and solemnity of the meeting.;
10 2. Exhibiting within one (1) mile, any shows or plays without a
11 license by the proper authority. Knowingly obstructing, detaining,
12 hindering, impeding, or blocking the entry of another person to or
13 exit from a place where such meeting is held;
14 3. Engaging in, or aiding or promoting within the like
15 distance, any racing of animals or gaming of any description.
16 Knowingly approaching another person within eight (8) feet of such
17 person, unless such other person consents, for the purpose of
18 passing a leaflet or handbill to, displaying a sign to, or engaging
19 in oral protest, education, or counseling with such other person in
20 the public way or sidewalk area within a radius of one hundred (100)
21 feet from any entrance door to a place where the meeting is held; or
22 4. Obstructing in any manner, without authority of law, within
23 the like distance one (1) mile, the free passage along any highway
24 to the place of such the meeting.
